Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating possible renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting renal dysfunction, possibly with tubular involvement. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, making diabetes less likely. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for underlying renal pathology.
